on may explain the\nvelocity widths of emission lines associated with high redshift radio galaxies,\nif the environmental temperature is lower, or the jet-ambient density ratio is\nless extreme than in their low redshift counterparts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Oct 2006 17:53:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Dec 2006 12:42:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
